social_posts.post_text: Feeling pretty damn grateful to have such talented, inspiring, badass women in my life⚡️

Devastated.  All we talked about throughout the few days of this shoot, was our families.  We reminisced of our days dancing in the parking garage of our apartment building and how far we had both come since then.  How happy we both were.  We couldn’t stop talking about our kids.  Such good energy.  Such a kind human.  Such a light.  Gone too soon💔

Treasured moments🔺
Treasured friendships❤️

Counting my blessings🔺

#christmas22

As I was reflecting on 2022, I decided I wanted to document this epic year of travel.  I’ve never made a video before, so bare with me. There’s a first time for everything, right?! I wanted to share a glimpse into what my year looked like🔺
Everyone has things that make them tick.  For my family, it’s travel & adventure. 
When Lola was born, we decided to put an end to meaningless gifts for holidays & birthdays. Instead, we find cool places to travel to & adventures to go on.
It’s been 8 years now of exploring with Lola. She brings a whole new level of excitement to it all. She’s already traveled to 23 states & 3 countries in counting! Taking her places we’ve been & seeing it through her eyes, is so incredible.  Exploring places together for the first time, is even better! There really is nothing like it.  We filled our passports before having her, & now we are going to make sure she fills hers.  She drove cross country & back with us when she was 5.  I remember people telling us we were nuts!  But the truth is, she is a reflection of us.  She loves it just as much as we do.  There is So much growth & perspective we’ve gained through traveling together.  To swing on the swings of the Eiffel Tower holding hands with my little girl, or watch it at dusk as it begins to sparkle, are moments that have completely taken my breathe away.  These are the moments I live for.  It’s nothing you can read in a book or watch on a movie. It’s gonna be a hard year to top, but we are up for the challenge.
I’m so grateful to get to do what I love every day.  I’m grateful for all the people who believe in me & give me opportunities that allow me to live the life of my dreams.  I’m excited for what’s to come!! 2023, I’m ready for ya! 
⚡️Coming soon:Our travel channel⚡️

Well, here we are after another adventure together.  Watching the sunset on your first day being 8!  Today, your birthday wish in Hawaii was to swim with Sea Turtles and drink out of a Pineapple. ☑️☑️
My girl, you are all things good.  I am amazed with who you are, and who you are becoming.  You teach me the most profound things, in the most subtle of ways.  I really can’t put into words or even grasp this unique bond we share.  But I know it is what I live for.
This year was filled with the most magical experiences together.  Finally getting to take you to other countries over the summer, was the most epic of them all.  You graduated from a Daisy to a Brownie this year I’m Girlscouts.  It’s been so nostalgic for me and such a gift:) You’ve started training in singing this year, and I’m loving every second hearing your beautiful voice😭You are also playing keys now in a band at School of Rock.  Seeing you thrive in this realm has been really exciting👏🏻 Had someone told me THIS is what 8 looks like for you, it would’ve blown me away.  Rightly so.  Because I watch you do all these things, and I’m so incredibly impressed and taken back by ALL that is YOU, Lola Grey.  You are such an old soul and so darn smart. I can barely keep up with all your questions and your inquisitive nature.  Your empathy in life has often brought tears to my eyes.  You are by far the coolest kid, and I can’t believe I get to be your mom❤️ Im so excited to see what this next trip around the sun will bring for you.  I love you more then all the stars ✨

S U P E R  N I N T E N D O  W O R L D 

My 8 bit childhood has come to life. 

As an 80s/90s kid, a good amount of my childhood was spent with a controller in my hand. The days a having to memorize each level to try and make it through unscathed as long as possible, because there was no save game. You lost and were sent back to the beginning to do it all over again. But oh what a feeling, when you finally did make it to the end. Defeated the final boss, saved the Princess, and returned order to the world. No better feeling at the time. 

So much fun sharing my love for video games with my daughter. She has shown a substantial interest in what Jeni and I both did when we were kids. She thinks it’s hilarious how crude the 8 bit characters were on the NES. 

Running around punching blocks and collecting coins with the power band in a life size mushroom kingdom is so much fun. Every detail is well thought out and we left in awe of what was able to be created here. 🍄

A few months ago, Lola entered a writing contest called Young Authors. There is 1 winner picked for every grade that gets their story published in a book for the school library.  Lola worked so hard on this.  It was the first time she ever came to me about something that she wanted to win.  I asked her if she needed any help brainstorming and she said she wasn’t allowed to work on it at home and get help from a parent.  She also informed me, “she didn’t want what was in my head, to be in her head and possibly change her ideas.” (👏🏻) After she turned it in, I waited every day in anticipation.  One day at pickup, she jumped in my car and screamed telling me she had won.  We both screamed!! I may have cried a little too. 
The next step, was illustrating every page of her book.  Today, she received an award and her copy of the book at an awards ceremony😍 Along with her final reading award surpassing her end of year goal.  I’m pretty damn proud❤️

To the dad who knows he has to hold his daughters hair tightly in one hand, while brushing with the other, just so that it doesn’t hurt.  Thank you for always taking the time.  Sometimes, time consists of reading Harry Potter so she can fall asleep (now on the 5th book) and other times, it’s to learn how to do her hair for dance and make sure those ponytails are even 👏🏻 You ALWAYS take the time.  When I sign up every year to be Lolas room parent in school and decorate her classroom every month and throw a party for every holiday, you jump in to help and never complain. 
No matter how much I take on, you are there by my side every second of the way. 
You put so much of yourself in everything you do for her (and us). We both love you for so many reasons…but today, we celebrate you for being such a kick ass dad.  Lola is one lucky little girl🔺 Happy Fathers Day @ryan_novak

We had a big moment this weekend and I couldn’t be more proud.  In august, Lola auditioned for her first musical and landed the lead role as Matilda at the Youth Academy of Dramatic Arts.  Since then, she has put her heart and soul into learning the script, songs and choreography. Her commitment at 8 years old has been so admirable, to say the least.  I’m proud of her for going after something she wanted and for working her butt off once she got it! Getting to rehearse with her these past 8 weeks has been the most special time that i’ll never forget❤️

Prior to having Lola, Ryan and I toured the world exploring 36 countries to date.  Once we had Lola, we began to show her the world as well.  She loves it just as much as us and we realized quickly that we all grow & thrive the most, when traveling.  We began documenting our journey together both in and out of the country & have started our own travel channel.
From snowmobiling through the forrest in the longest trail in the country, to climbing the stairs of the Eiffel Tower, we are sharing our experiences. 
Our first video is up, one of our all time favorite cities of the world….LONDON. (LINK IN BIO)
If you’re into this kind of content, consider a like & subscribing.

My girl, this year feels like a flash.  It’s tough to wrap my head around all the growth that’s taken place.  I sure wish it would just SLOW DOWN.  9 years old today.

We are currently visiting your 4th country, Mexico.  Until a week ago, it was supposed to be Australia, but the weather had other plans:/ So instead of holding a Koala today, we switched gears…you SWAM with DOLPHINS!! What a moment that was😍

Speaking of moments… proudest mom moment to date happened during 8.  I got to see you go after something you really wanted this year and come through with shining colors⚡️You auditioned and got the role of Matilda in your 1st musical.  It was such a proud moment for me, but it wasn’t because you got the lead…(even though that made fireworks go off inside of me that came out in the form of tears)…it was the hard work and commitment you put into it that impressed me the most.  It gave me a sense of ease seeing you want something, go after it, and give it your all EVERY step of the way.  If you can do this at 8, you will do this at any age!  You blew me away and I have never been more proud of you👏🏻

Let’s talk about our conversations.  I may or may not have had to start googling in order to keep up with you and your questions😅 I’m floored sometimes by the things you think about.  I feel so lucky to be on the receiving end of all that’s in your mind and heart❤️ 
  The glimpses of the person you are becoming, continue to fill light into every space of my being.  Thank you for being a continual source of inspiration and drive.  I’m so grateful I get to be your mom. 
Happy Birthday my girl 🔺
